Wildflower Experiment

Joanna Tang

12/20/2020

CCBER Wildflower Experiment

Seed Scarification Treatments

H1: Seed scarification treatment has an effect on the number of seedlings germinated. Results: No significant difference in the number of seedlings germinated. H1 not supported.

Caging Treatments

H2: Caging treatment has an effect on the number of seedlings germinated. Results: Caging treatment only favored seedling germination of Lupinus succulentus. H2 partially supported.
